    "recap_headline": "University of Northern Colorado Athletics",
    "recap_text": "OMAHA, Neb.\n\u2013 Northern Colorado battled through an offensive back-and-forth on Saturday afternoon but ultimately came up just short in an 11-inning thriller, falling 12-11 to Omaha at Tal Anderson Field. With the result, the Bears even the series at one game apiece and will look to claim the rubber match tomorrow.\nUNC jumped out to an early advantage, plating four runs across the first two innings to take control. The Bears capitalized on timely hitting and early pressure on the base paths, building a 4-0 lead before Omaha began to respond.\nThe Mavericks answered in the middle innings, highlighted by a three-run home run in the fifth to take their first lead of the game. However, the Bears responded in the sixth inning, erupting for five runs to regain momentum and build a 9-5 advantage.\nBrandon Sanchez\nand\nMason Griffin\nled the offensive charge, each delivering key extra-base hits. Griffin finished with three hits and three RBIs, including a game-tying home run in the eighth and a go-ahead RBI double in the 10th.\nSam Pease\nadded a standout performance at the plate as well, going 4-for-5 with two RBIs and three runs scored.\nOmaha answered once again in the sixth with a five-run inning of its own, tying the game at 10-10 and setting the stage for extra innings.\nAfter Griffin's RBI double in the 10th gave Northern Colorado an 11-10 edge, the Mavericks responded in the bottom half to extend the game. In the 11th, Omaha used a triple and a walk-off single to secure the 12-11 victory.\nON DECK:\nThe Bears aim to take game three on Sunday and clinch the series against the Mavericks. First pitch is set for 1 p.m. MDT.\nDIAMOND CLUB\nThe Diamond Club plays a vital role in supporting the UNC Baseball program. By giving to the Diamond Club, you help provide access to facility enhancements\u2014such as the Jackson Field Turf Project\u2014along with advanced technology and elevated daily operations, giving our student-athletes the resources to compete and excel at the highest level.\nGive to the Diamond Club today!\nFOLLOW THE BEARS\nFor complete coverage of UNC Athletics, visit uncbears.com. Follow the baseball team on X (formerly Twitter) (@UNC_BearsBSB) and Instagram (@UNC_BearsBaseball).",
